rComments: This class makes you think a lot about the nature of OB. Many students like to be spoon-fed the answers, hence their lack of interest in the course. Prof R, tries her best to address students needs who go out of their way to get help. The course is very broad, hence can be difficult but if you put the effort into studying, a good mark is possible.
awful, avoid her for sure, makes everything over complicated which is totally unnecessary, poor prof

The worse prof I have ever had in this uni so far. Her grading criteria is a huge confusion. Everything needs to be done with her preference. Assignments are useless. No creativity allowed at all. She doesn't like students to have questions. I deeply regret having my first exposure of OB with her. It killed all my interest in going into HR stream.

She was extremely confusing with the work she assigns, she even included a wrong rubric/assignment sheet for a group presentation that was worth 25%. Her classes arent very helpful at all, it feels like we are just playing ice-breakers every single week. She is unable to answer questions effectively, redirects it/makes you look through the textbook

Her lectures are often very hard to follow. She goes through a number of slides very fast and it is often hard to understand concepts. She does not explain concepts very well and her humor is overrated.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Assigned problems to complete during class but did not give enough time to complete the tasks before moving to the next topic. Together with her scattered lecture style that basically makes the slides useless, it is impossible to absorb anything from her lectures. Self-study is key in her class. Also micro-manages.

Her activities makes the class very interesting and participatory. One of the kindest teachers I've ever known. I don't know if it's her TA's or herself that grade our assignments and tests, but they sure do give you marks. Not easy, but definitely not hard. OB is heavily based on test banks.
Professor marks are scattered, lecture style is scattered leaving class not retaining much. Marking for assignments have no standard and marks based on class favorites.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Best prof I've ever met in utsc. Knows what she's talking about, very professional in her field, passionate to communicate with students and willing to solve problems. Everyone will learn a lot from this course!!  For sure to take it!!

I took Negotiation with this prof. Best. class. ever! Each class has a theme and all you need to do is follow that theme. You MUST actively participate in the class discussions and prepare your scenarios beforehand. Assignments are easy all you need to do is prepare and use her notes. Final is a bit heavy. you need the readings all done for this.

rComments: Worst prof I've ever had. So rude and condescending when you ask for clarification. Everything is self-taught. She doesn't do remarks for your midterm even if you feel you have just cause.
very unwilling to help students and has class favourites.
WARNING: if you have to take this class, don't take it with her.
not helpful, not clear, very vague and basic coverage.

rComments: Not sure why people dislike her, low marks perhaps? I have yet to receive my final mark, but assignments are marked fairly, the exams are fair, she's as engaging as she can be (given the boring subject matter), and she's willing to help if you seek it. Great prof :-)

Followed what she wanted for our presentation. Asked for advice on what she wanted for the paper after the presentation. She still gives us a low mark (60s) with comments contradicting what she says she wanted. Do not, under any circumstances, take anything with her. Your grades will fall and you'll have no idea why.

She is a researcher before a lecturer. Her teaching style is high school. Not fond of what I learnt in class; dry stuff. At least her coursework was not demanding. Very biased, micro-manages like crazy, prepare to follow what SHE wants for the research report and don't do anything excess for the presentation. Helps if she knows you = more marks.

Horrible HORRIBLE Prof. Do not take ANYTHING with her. Take any required management courses with Hugh McDonald instead. She sucks at teaching, you learn NOTHING in her class and if you dont follow her way of everything, you will fail her course. I learnt NOTHING from her what so ever. And she goes on her cellphone while marking for presentations!-

Truley one of the lesser profs among the vibrant staff of UTSC.  She successfully turned a class that could potentially be interesting into trash.  Her standards are: "if you don't do it exactly the way I would do it, you are definitely wrong."  Being a course that is based on much subjectivity, you will suffer if you have indepedent thought.

Godzilla of Micromanaging!!  Every single worksheet that is suppose to "help" us to adopt to her mandatory style of learning is required to be handed in for credit worth 0.25%-2%.  NO freedom, no autonomy, no creativity.  All out of the box answers are not encouraged.  btw.. her voice is annoying...
very good
